longBusinessSummary: Carlyle Commodities Corp. engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral resource properties in Canada. It primarily explores for iron, titanium, and vanadium deposits. The company has an option to acquire 100% interest in the Sunset mining property consisting of four claims covering an area of approximately 785.31 hectares located in Vancouver, British Columbia. It also holds interests in the Star, Porcher, Blackie, and Peneece vanadium properties located in northwestern British Columbia. The company was formerly known as Delrey Metals Corp. and changed its name to Carlyle Commodities Corp. in February 2020. Carlyle Commodities Corp. was incorporated in 2017 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
